  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "Certainly! English music is rich with memorable and impactful lyrics that have resonated with audiences over the years. Here are some of the best lines from English songs, spanning various genres and eras:\n\n1. **\"And in the end, the love you take is equal to the love you make.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"The End\" by The Beatles*  \n   A profound reflection on reciprocity and the essence of love.\n\n2. **\"Is this the real life? Is this just fantasy?\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen*  \n   An iconic opening that sets the stage for the song's epic narrative.\n\n3. **\"You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Imagine\" by John Lennon*  \n   A hopeful vision for a better, more unified world.\n\n4. **\"Every breath you take, every move you make, I'll be watching you.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Every Breath You Take\" by The Police*  \n   A haunting portrayal of obsession and surveillance.\n\n5. **\"Don't stop believin', hold on to that feeling.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Don't Stop Believin'\" by Journey*  \n   An enduring anthem of hope and perseverance.\n\n6. **\"There's a lady who's sure all that glitters is gold.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin*  \n   A poetic inquiry into materialism and spiritual longing.\n\n7. **\"I can't get no satisfaction.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction\" by The Rolling Stones*  \n   A rebellious statement against unmet desires and societal norms.\n\n8. **\"Hello from the other side, I must've called a thousand times.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Hello\" by Adele*  \n   A poignant expression of longing and missed connections.\n\n9. **\"We don't need no education.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Another Brick in the Wall (Part 2)\" by Pink Floyd*  \n   A critique of oppressive educational systems and authoritarianism.\n\n10. **\"You're the one that I want, ooh ooh ooh, honey.\"**  \n    *\u2014 \"You're the One That I Want\" from Grease*  \n    A catchy, energetic declaration of attraction and desire.\n\n11. **\"Isn't she lovely, isn't she wonderful.\"**  \n    *\u2014 \"Isn't She Lovely\" by Stevie Wonder*  \n    A joyful celebration of love and the beauty of life.\n\n12. **\"I still haven't found what I'm looking for.\"**  \n    *\u2014 \"I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For\" by U2*  \n    A contemplative quest for meaning and fulfillment.\n\nThese lines are celebrated not only for their poetic quality but also for their ability to capture complex emotions and universal themes. Whether inspiring, questioning, or simply resonating on a personal level, these lyrics have left a lasting impact on listeners around the world.",
